answers.body_markdown:
# Problem

- JLink does not work with [automatic modules][1] (i.e. packages without a module-info.java file)

# Steps

## Copy dependencies to {build_folder}/dependency using [maven-dependency-plugin][2]

```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
	&lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
	&lt;artifactId&gt;maven-dependency-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
	&lt;version&gt;3.6.0&lt;/version&gt;
	&lt;executions&gt;
		&lt;execution&gt;
			&lt;id&gt;copy&lt;/id&gt;
			&lt;phase&gt;package&lt;/phase&gt;
			&lt;goals&gt;
				&lt;goal&gt;copy-dependencies&lt;/goal&gt;
			&lt;/goals&gt;
		&lt;/execution&gt;
	&lt;/executions&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```

## Add module-info for automatic modules using [moditect-maven-plugin][3]

```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
	&lt;groupId&gt;org.moditect&lt;/groupId&gt;
	&lt;artifactId&gt;moditect-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
	&lt;version&gt;1.0.0.Final&lt;/version&gt;
	&lt;executions&gt;
		&lt;execution&gt;
			&lt;id&gt;add-module-infos&lt;/id&gt;
			&lt;phase&gt;generate-resources&lt;/phase&gt;
			&lt;goals&gt;
				&lt;goal&gt;add-module-info&lt;/goal&gt;
			&lt;/goals&gt;
			&lt;configuration&gt;
				&lt;outputDirectory&gt;
					${project.build.directory}/dependency
				&lt;/outputDirectory&gt;
				&lt;modules&gt;
					&lt;module&gt;
						&lt;artifact&gt;
							&lt;groupId&gt;commons-io&lt;/groupId&gt;
							&lt;artifactId&gt;commons-io&lt;/artifactId&gt;
							&lt;version&gt;2.13.0&lt;/version&gt;
						&lt;/artifact&gt;
						&lt;moduleInfoSource&gt;
							module org.apache.commons.io {
							exports org.apache.commons.io;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.build;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.charset;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.comparator;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.file;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.file.attribute;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.file.spi;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.filefilter;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.function;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.input;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.input.buffer;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.monitor;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.output;
							exports org.apache.commons.io.serialization;

							}

						&lt;/moduleInfoSource&gt;
					&lt;/module&gt;
				&lt;/modules&gt;
				&lt;overwriteExistingFiles&gt;true&lt;/overwriteExistingFiles&gt;
			&lt;/configuration&gt;
		&lt;/execution&gt;

	&lt;/executions&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```

### How to get the `&lt;moduleInfoSource&gt;` content?

- go to the folder with the required (dependency) .jar file
- If you use Intellij IDEA, in project view, there&#39;s a section named `External Libraries`. Double-click on the entry, right click on the `.jar`, open in -&gt; Explorer.
- open command prompt in that folder
- `jdeps -generate-module-info . {jar_file_name}.jar`
- Make sure the PATH environment variable is correct
- open the generated `module-info.java` file with a text editor and copy the content
- paste to the `&lt;moduleInfoSource&gt;` section

## Create runtime image (with jlink, in the backend)

- please change the `&lt;modules&gt;`, `&lt;launcher&gt;`sections according to your project information.
- If your module is non-modular, it is important that the main class does not  extend `javafx.Application` directly. We can create a launcher class which looks like this (reference pending):

&gt; launcher class
```java
public class Launcher {  
    public static void main(String[] args) {  
        HelloApplication.main(args);  
    }  
}
```

&gt; pom.xml
```xml
&lt;execution&gt;
	&lt;id&gt;create-runtime-image&lt;/id&gt;
	&lt;phase&gt;package&lt;/phase&gt;
	&lt;goals&gt;
		&lt;goal&gt;create-runtime-image&lt;/goal&gt;
	&lt;/goals&gt;
	&lt;configuration&gt;
		&lt;jarInclusionPolicy&gt;APP_WITH_DEPENDENCIES&lt;/jarInclusionPolicy&gt;
		&lt;modulePath&gt;
			&lt;path&gt;${project.build.directory}/${project.artifactId}-${project.version}.${project.packaging}&lt;/path&gt;
			&lt;path&gt;${project.build.directory}/dependency&lt;/path&gt;
		&lt;/modulePath&gt;
		&lt;modules&gt;
			&lt;module&gt;com.example.soone&lt;/module&gt;
		&lt;/modules&gt;
		&lt;launcher&gt;
			&lt;name&gt;hello&lt;/name&gt;
			&lt;module&gt;com.example.soone/com.example.soone.Launcher&lt;/module&gt;
		&lt;/launcher&gt;
		&lt;outputDirectory&gt;
			${project.build.directory}/jlink-image
		&lt;/outputDirectory&gt;
	&lt;/configuration&gt;
&lt;/execution&gt;
```

&gt; [link to demo repository][4]


# Recommendation

- I suggest changing the build system to Gradle, it works better with automatic modules and you won&#39;t have to manually figure out the dependencies, saves a lot of time especially when working with JavaFX.


  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46741907/what-is-an-automatic-module
  [2]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-dependency-plugin/
  [3]: https://github.com/moditect/moditect#adding-module-descriptors-to-existing-jar-files
  [4]: https://github.com/0100Light/so-javafx-moditect

