                    + &quot;joined queue &quot; +  i);
        }

**And now, the main idea:**

The main idea is to run the simulation one-clock-tick-at-a-time until all queues are empty, just as you coded in the main loop. With each tick we want to do two things:

 - Add a customer or not, at random. This code generates a random `double` in the range [0.0, 1.0). If the generated number exceeds `PROBABILITY_CUSTOMER_JOINS`, the customer is not added. 
 - Decrease the remaining transaction time for the first customer in each lane by one tick. If a remaining time reaches zero, the transaction is complete, and the customer leaves the queue. 

             for (int time = 1; !allQueuesEmpty(checkoutLines);  time++) {
                if (     Customer.nextID &lt; MAX_CUSTOMERS 
                      &amp;&amp; random.nextDouble() &lt; PROBABILITY_CUSTOMER_JOINS) {
